MBT-Based Electron Orbital Simulation
This simulation shows an electron's s-orbital distribution generated using MBT-inspired decay (motion-based tension falloff).
 
Code Used:

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D

def mbt_s_orbital_density(x, y, z, alpha=1.0):
    r = np.sqrt(x**2 + y**2 + z**2)
    return np.exp(-alpha * r)

grid_size = 100
lim = 5
x = np.linspace(-lim, lim, grid_size)
y = np.linspace(-lim, lim, grid_size)
z = np.linspace(-lim, lim, grid_size)
X, Y, Z = np.meshgrid(x, y, z)

density = mbt_s_orbital_density(X, Y, Z)
threshold = 0.3
mask = density > threshold

x_vals, y_vals, z_vals = X[mask], Y[mask], Z[mask]

fig = plt.figure()
ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')
ax.scatter(x_vals, y_vals, z_vals, c=density[mask], cmap='plasma', s=1)
plt.show()

